The body of the fourth missing teen has been found in Sea Point. The body can not be retrieved currently due to high seas and riptides. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The body of a fourth missing teen has been found in Sea Point on Tuesday. The body can't be retrieved currently due to high seas and riptides. The body of a 15-year-old boy was brought to shore on Sunday by three local surfers. WATCH: Eyewitness account of missing teens at Sea Point The bodies of a 15-year-old girl and a 16-year-old boy were found and recovered on Monday. Spokesperson for the NSRI, Craig Lambinon, said this time has been difficult for everyone involved. "Our care and thoughts are with the family and we have had the Fire and Rescue Service chaplain service assist with family counselling," Lambinon said.